message.content: <OUTPUT_TEXT>To call upon witnesses to testify at a hearing, you need to follow these steps: 1. Identify the witnesses whose testimony is relevant to the case. 2. Obtain their contact information and ensure their willingness to testify. 3. Prepare and serve subpoenas to compel their attendance if necessary. 4. Coordinate with the witnesses to confirm the date, time, and location of the hearing. 5. Brief the witnesses on the process and any legal considerations, ensuring they understand the importance of their testimony. 6. Ensure all logistical arrangements are in place for the witnesses to attend the hearing. 7. Prepare the witnesses for potential questioning by both your side and opposing counsel.</OUTPUT_TEXT>
